01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:10,150
I think I can die...

802
01:08:10,150 --> 01:08:13,130
without any regrets.

803
01:08:13,130 --> 01:08:17,590
Why do you keep saying stuff like that?

804
01:08:17,590 --> 01:08:19,950
I'm sorry.

805
01:08:19,950 --> 01:08:23,760
What I mean is...

806
01:08:25,980 --> 01:08:30,480
I'm so happy I could die.

807
01:08:30,480 --> 01:08:34,470
The fact that I'm with you like this.

808
01:08:50,040 --> 01:08:56,730
Dan Dan. I think your dad is opening up more.

809
01:08:56,740 --> 01:08:59,210
Just wait a little more.

810
01:08:59,210 --> 01:09:01,470
I think so too.

811
01:09:01,470 --> 01:09:07,140
He's not yelling at me to break up with the Chairman like before.

812
01:09:07,140 --> 01:09:09,540
Right?

813
01:09:12,370 --> 01:09:15,700
I told your dad too.

814
01:09:15,700 --> 01:09:18,620
I told him to approve of your relationship.

815
01:09:18,620 --> 01:09:21,230
Did you?

816
01:09:21,230 --> 01:09:23,040
Did you really say so?

817
01:09:23,040 --> 01:09:24,960
Yes.

818
01:09:26,890 --> 01:09:32,990
After watching you and Young Gook today,

819
01:09:32,990 --> 01:09:37,360
I realized how happy you looked.

820
01:09:37,400 --> 01:09:45,320
I don't know why I tried to separate you two all this time.

821
01:09:45,320 --> 01:09:48,440
I was so stupid.

822
01:09:48,500 --> 01:09:56,300
Thank you so much for finally understanding me.

823
01:10:01,660 --> 01:10:08,040
Me, too. Thank you, Dan Dan.

824
01:10:08,040 --> 01:10:12,930
Thank you for forgiving me.

825
01:10:12,930 --> 01:10:17,480
I'm so happy and thankful.

826
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:21,050
I can't stop crying.

827
01:10:24,200 --> 01:10:26,770
Mom.

828
01:10:37,170 --> 01:10:39,450
Mom.

829
01:10:39,450 --> 01:10:43,280
The surgery will go well.

830
01:10:46,230 --> 01:10:50,050
Then let's make sure we go to Jeju Island together.

831
01:10:50,050 --> 01:10:52,070
Okay?

832
01:10:53,590 --> 01:10:56,880
All right.

833
01:10:56,880 --> 01:10:59,540
Let's do that.

834
01:10:59,540 --> 01:11:07,110
Just the thought of it makes me so happy.

835
01:11:07,110 --> 01:11:11,790
My Dan Dan. My daughter.

836
01:11:34,010 --> 01:11:36,760
Mom?

837
01:11:45,330 --> 01:11:48,750
Where did she go?

838
01:11:55,270 --> 01:11:57,270
How strange.

839
01:11:57,270 --> 01:11:59,320
Where did she go?

840
01:11:59,320 --> 01:12:01,800
Did she go to the bathroom--

841
01:12:22,960 --> 01:12:27,490
Mom? Are you inside?

842
01:12:27,490 --> 01:12:29,880
Mom?

843
01:12:58,450 --> 01:13:00,650
Mom! Mom!

844
01:13:00,650 --> 01:13:02,470
Mom! Mom!

845
01:13:02,470 --> 01:13:04,190
Wake up, Mom!

846
01:13:04,190 --> 01:13:06,040
Mom! Mom!

847
01:13:06,040 --> 01:13:08,020
Please wake up! Mom!

848
01:13:08,020 --> 01:13:09,740
Wake up, Mom!

849
01:13:09,740 --> 01:13:12,450
Mom! Mom!

850
01:13:12,450 --> 01:13:14,140
Wake up!

851
01:13:14,140 --> 01:13:16,660
Mom! Oh, my gosh.

852
01:13:16,660 --> 01:13:17,870
What do I do? Mom!

853
01:13:17,870 --> 01:13:19,850
Please wake up.

854
01:13:19,850 --> 01:13:23,760
Mom! Please... Mom!

855
01:13:23,760 --> 01:13:27,350
Wake up, Mom!

856
01:13:27,350 --> 01:13:30,520
What do I do?

857
01:13:30,520 --> 01:13:38,220
♫ Why do you run away, love like a shy child ♫

858
01:13:38,220 --> 01:13:44,720
♫ In case I lose it, I hold it tight ♫

859
01:13:44,720 --> 01:13:52,020
♫ But love always runs away, chased by longing ♫

860
01:13:52,020 --> 01:13:58,820
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

861
01:13:58,820 --> 01:14:07,650
♫ I have to abandon the longing and the grieves ♫

862
01:14:07,650 --> 01:14:10,770
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

863
01:14:10,770 --> 01:14:14,510
I will allow Dan Dan to marry you, Chairman.

864
01:14:14,510 --> 01:14:18,050
I finally got approval to marry Ms. Park from her father.

865
01:14:18,050 --> 01:14:19,890
How are you going to propose to Ms. Park?

866
01:14:19,890 --> 01:14:25,360
I already bought the ring, but I've been deliberating very seriously about how to propose.

867
01:14:25,360 --> 01:14:27,260
What? What's going on?

868
01:14:27,260 --> 01:14:30,950
Why isn't he taking the ring out? He must want to propose at a quiet place.

869
01:14:30,950 --> 01:14:32,310
What did you say, Oppa?

870
01:14:32,310 --> 01:14:33,960
Like I said, your share is left untouched.

871
01:14:33,960 --> 01:14:36,230
Se Ryun's share has been untouched?

872
01:14:36,230 --> 01:14:42,560
I'm not going to return to Korea again. I think this is the best I can do for everyone.

873
01:14:42,560 --> 01:14:44,050
What's up with Chairman?

874
01:14:44,050 --> 01:14:47,580
Is he thinking of skipping the proposal?

875
01:14:47,580 --> 01:14:49,870
I'm not going to marry you, Chairman!

876
01:14:49,870 --> 01:14:53,140
Ms. Park! What? She's not going to marry me?

877
01:14:53,140 --> 01:14:54,300
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫
